## VVS1 Diamond Price Scaling: The Carat-Weight Clarity Rule

As carat weight increases, a diamond's facets become physically larger. This is not a theory — it is optical physics. A 0.50ct diamond's table facet has a surface area roughly 4x smaller than a 2ct diamond's table. Inclusions that are genuinely invisible at 0.50ct occupy proportionally more visual space at 2ct.

